{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow more school pupils to repeat an academic year due to COVID-19 lockdown.",
        "additional_details": "Schooling provides essential learning and when schools close, children and youth are deprived opportunities for growth and development. The disadvantages are disproportionate for under-privileged learners...  (Quote taken from the UNESCO website). \r\n\r\nIf repeating a year was made more accessible & became more common, the issues over the impact to self confidence would be reduced. Thousands of children\u2019s future would be brighter. Especially those young in an academic year, vulnerable or with SEN.",
        "background": "Parents/guardians should have the right to have their child repeat an academic year. \r\n\r\nDue to the COVID crises many children would benefit from the ability to repeat a year. Currently it\u2019s unusual for a state school pupil to repeat an academic year & requires council approval. Review the paradigm.",
